  "texts": [
    "In the EU, the focus has been on establishing frameworks that ensure the ethical use of AI, focusing on data privacy, transparency, and accountability.",
    "The proposed regulations aim to categorize AI systems according to their risk levels and apply the corresponding oversight measures.",
    "China, on the other hand, has focused on harnessing the potential of GenAI while safeguarding national security and social stability.",
    "The Chinese approach includes stringent data control measures and guidelines to prevent the misuse of AI technologies, especially in areas like surveillance and censorship.These divergent approaches reflect the complexities and varying priorities in GenAI governance, illustrating the challenges in creating a universally accepted regulatory framework.",
    "The policies in these regions are likely to influence global standards and practices in the GenAI domain [14]."
